<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - world]]></title><link/> https://www.wsj.com/news/world <atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/wsj/en-us/world" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - world - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RS集线器</generator><webmaster>i@diygod.me (DIYgod)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 7 月 21 日星期五 09:44:06 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[Untangling the U.S. From China’s Economy Is Messy]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>珍妮特·耶伦的“朋友外包”推动因供应链纵横交错而变得复杂<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001071011"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="574" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819897?width=860&amp;height=574" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">作为美国稳定关系努力的一部分，财政部长珍妮特·耶伦本月访问了北京。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：托马斯·彼得/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001071011"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/andrew-duehren" itemprop="url" rel="author">安德鲁·杜伦</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 21 日上午 5:30 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/untangling-the-u-s-from-chinas-economy-is-messy-8a658f2e"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>越南河内——事实证明，拜登政府通过外科手术式切断与中国经济关系的尝试很难执行。</p><p>美国财政部长珍妮特·耶伦本周访问了越南，讨论她推动的“ <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/yellen-calls-for-friend-shoring-trade-to-diversify-from-china-11658200959?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">友岸外包</a>”，她用这个术语呼吁企业将供应链从中国转移到更友好的国家。过去五年，美国和越南之间的贸易额呈爆炸式增长，从 2018 年的 600 亿美元增至 2022 年的约 1400 亿美元。</p><p> “我们看到了深化这些关系的巨大潜力，”耶伦在参观河内一家依赖中国零部件的工厂时表示。她在访问期间与越南总理范明正和其他共产党官员的会面中多次赞扬了两国不断发展的关系。</p><p>厘清中国在全球供应链中的角色，即使是在有限的领域，也绝非易事。近年来，美国从<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-imported-more-cars-phones-supplies-from-abroad-9157aca6?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">中国进口的商品份额有所下降</a>，而从其他亚洲国家的进口份额则有所扩大。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=EA224A41-9ED5-4FFE-94DD-F6BDB9AE59AB&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Funtangling-the-u-s-from-chinas-economy-is-messy-8a658f2e&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">美国财政部长珍妮特·耶伦周日结束对中国的访问时表示，双方在应对经济和国家安全紧张局势方面正在取得进展。她补充说，世界上最大的两个经济体脱钩是“不可能的”。照片：Mark R. Crisino/Zuma Press<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>越南或韩国等许多替代贸易伙伴本身就与中国有着紧密的联系。中国在清洁能源技术方面的主导地位使得拜登政府对于推动企业完全避开中国产品犹豫不决。准确识别美国及其盟国认为中国构成威胁的行业具有挑战性。</p><p>本月早些时候，耶伦在北京<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/yellen-says-u-s-doesnt-seek-winner-take-all-fight-with-china-72ab3c95?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">告诉中国同行</a>，美国的目标是减少关键领域对中国的敞口，同时不损害对两国有利的贸易和投资流动。</p><h3>友好伙伴与中国保持密切联系</h3><p>越南的生产在很多情况下仍然涉及中国公司。</p><p>在河内，耶伦参观了生产电动摩托车的 Selex Motors 工厂。该公司首席执行官表示，该公司使用中国供应商生产电动机以及一些电子连接器、开关和减震器。他说，公司80%的供应来自当地。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>美国是否应该继续寻求与中国经济脱钩？为什么或者为什么不？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>越南已成为美国太阳能电池板的重要供应国</p><p>不过，商务部的一项调查发现， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-solar-manufacturers-dodged-u-s-tariffs-probe-finds-11669952820?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国公司通过将产品改道越南和其他三个东南亚国家来规避关税</a>。</p><p>这一发现将使来自越南和其他国家的太阳能电池板征收大幅更高的关税，但拜登政府因担心美国太阳能电池板成本上涨<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-administration-to-waive-solar-import-tariffs-for-two-years-11654525408?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">而推迟了征税</a></p><p>一位财政部高级官员表示，中国企业并未参与美国和越南之间贸易增长的大部分，并指出越南有利的经济条件推动了经济增长。</p><p>美国<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/new-ev-rules-mean-fewer-models-eligible-for-tax-credit-98b6b63c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">为帮助消费者购买电动汽车提供</a>新补贴，旨在减少对中国的依赖，同时减少碳排放，但也面临着类似的挑战。为了获得补贴资格，汽车的电池必须主要由来自美国或其自由贸易伙伴之一的零部件和矿物制成。中国不是这样的合作伙伴。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="468" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820752?width=700&amp;height=468" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">拜登总统去年参观了韩国三星半导体工厂。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：乔纳森·恩斯特/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><h3>美国尚未确定哪些公司值得关注</h3><p>即将出台的规则将进一步完善这些要求，禁止使用包含来自“相关外国实体”的任何材料的电池。</p><p>无论拜登政府广泛定义“受关注外国实体”以包括许多中国供应商，还是更狭隘地将其仅针对某些公司，都将对信贷的可用性产生巨大影响。 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-controls-minerals-that-run-the-worldand-just-fired-a-warning-shot-at-u-s-5961d77b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国公司在电池组件的制造和其中的矿物供应方面占据主导地位</a>。对于汽车制造商来说，在不久的将来将中国产品完全从供应链中剔除可能是不可能的。一些美国公司甚至<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ford-invests-3-5-billion-in-michigan-battery-plant-with-chinese-partners-technology-1aed174c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">计划与中国公司合作</a>生产电池。</p><p>耶伦在接受采访时表示，定义“受关注的外国实体”“相当复杂”，并补充说，财政部的规则将保持在《通胀削减法案》的范围内。</p><p> “但在有一定范围的地方，我们当然要记住，我们不想让它变得不可能——过于关注供应链的弹性，以至于我们无法实现让汽车上路的任何目标，”耶伦说。</p><p>在其他清洁能源补贴方面，拜登政府制定的规则对采购要求的规定比一些美国制造商所希望的更为宽松，为在补贴清洁能源建设中使用中国供应扫清了道路。尽管美国实施出口管制，拜登政府还<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-to-allow-south-korean-taiwan-chip-makers-to-keep-operations-in-china-5d7d72cc?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">允许韩国和台湾的顶级半导体制造商</a>继续向中国销售产品。</p><p>拜登政府还在制定<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-grapples-with-potential-threats-from-chinese-ai-7d1f2e70?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">限制美国对华部分投资</a>的新规则，但仍在整理这些规则如何适用于美国公司的外国子公司等细节。这些限制将适用于美国在半导体、量子计算和人工智能领域的私募股权和风险投资，禁止对这些领域的某些投资，同时要求披露其他领域的投资。</p><p>该命令的目的是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-prepares-new-rules-on-investment-in-technology-abroad-a451e035?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">阻止美国投资者</a>帮助中国公司开发可用于在军事对抗中对抗美国或其盟友的技术。</p><p> “这还没有最终决定，所以我不想说它会发生，但我相信它会发生，而且我认为今年夏天最有可能发生，”耶伦在接受采访时谈到新的投资规则时表示。</p><p>美国正在鼓励其欧洲盟友采取类似措施来保护供应链并限制北京获得西方专业知识。事实证明，找到正确的平衡点对他们来说也很困难。</p><p> “我们需要与中国进行贸易，同时我们需要让关键的战略供应链更加安全，”欧盟经济委员保罗·真蒂洛尼(Paolo Gentiloni)在接受采访时表示。 “说起来简单，但实际操作起来并不明显。”</p><p>写信给安德鲁·杜伦 (Andrew Duehren)，邮箱为<a href="mailto:andrew.duehren@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">andrew.duehren@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 21 Jul 2023 09:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/untangling-the-us-from-chinas-economy-is-messy-8a658f2e</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/untangling-the-us-from-chinas-economy-is-messy-8a658f2e<author><![CDATA[Andrew Duehren]]></author><category>电气元件/设备</category><category>工业电子</category><category>工业品</category><category>技术</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>供应链</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>珍妮特·耶伦</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>供应链</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>电气元件</category><category>设备</category><category>工业电子</category><category>工业品</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Russia Seeks to Divert Ukrainian Forces Away From Counteroffensive]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>随着乌克兰军队向南部和东部推进，俄罗斯向北部发起攻势<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820282/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="最近，乌克兰东北部城镇莱曼附近，一枚乌克兰榴弹炮向一辆俄罗斯坦克开火。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>最近，乌克兰东北部城镇莱曼附近，一枚乌克兰榴弹炮向一辆俄罗斯坦克开火。 <span></span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001070298"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001070298"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者：<span class="author" itemprop="name">奥克萨娜·格里岑科</span>Emanuele Satolli 为《华尔街日报》拍摄的照片</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 21 日凌晨 3:30 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-seeks-to-divert-ukrainian-forces-away-from-counteroffensive-80580e89"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>乌克兰莱曼——当乌克兰军队发动<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-adopts-slow-approach-to-counteroffensive-our-problem-everywhere-is-the-sky-a2e51d7a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">缓慢且代价高昂的反攻</a>，以夺回该国南部和东部被俄罗斯占领的领土时，莫斯科军队正在乌克兰东北部的一角进行反击，试图转移基辅军队的注意力。</p><p> “他们不断地试图前进，但我们却在反击，”驻扎在东北部城镇莱曼附近丘陵地带的榴弹炮连指挥官亚历山大·日塔尔中尉说。</p><p>最近一天，一辆俄罗斯坦克威胁到日塔尔的阵地，这位戴着耳环的 21 岁苗条男子必须快速行动。</p><p>在通过星链连接到互联网的平板电脑上绘制出坦克的位置后，Zhytar 下达了开火命令。一门乌克兰的“格沃兹迪卡”自行榴弹炮从附近的树林中出现，快速发射了两发子弹，使坦克暂时撤退。</p><p>最近几周，在前线以及更远的北部，俄罗斯军队对乌克兰军队发动了多次袭击。乌克兰官员警告说，俄罗斯正在北部城市库皮扬斯克附近集结军队， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraines-eastern-advance-puts-forces-close-to-key-town-11662718470?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">基辅军队在去年秋天的闪电攻势中从莫斯科重新夺回了该城市</a>。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820297?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">指挥驻扎在莱曼附近的榴弹炮连的亚历山大·日塔尔中尉最近瞄准了一辆俄罗斯坦克的坐标。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>其目的是防止基辅向南部其他战线部署更多部队和装备，乌克兰军队正在那里攻击俄罗斯的据点，作为利用西方训练和装备的部队进行反攻的一部分。虽然进展缓慢，但乌克兰军队最近占领了巴赫穆特周围的大部分主要高地，威胁到俄罗斯对两个月前经过漫长而血腥的城市战斗后<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/36-hours-in-bakhmut-one-units-desperate-battle-to-hold-back-the-russians-72e30f01?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">占领的东部城市</a>的控制。</p><p>乌克兰国防部副部长汉娜·马利亚尔本周表示：“就在我们采取主动并开始推进后，敌人立即在其他方向活跃起来，以分散我们的注意力并分散兵力。”</p><p>乌克兰武装部队发言人谢尔希·切雷瓦蒂上校最近在电视节目中表示，莱曼周边地区是东线遭受炮击最严重的地区。 “敌人在那里集中了一支强大的空降兵和步兵部队，”他说。</p><p> 7月8日早上，俄罗斯军队用多管火箭炮轰击了莱曼市的一个街头市场，之后人行道上的血迹仍然清晰可见。据警方称，至少八人死亡，十几人受伤。</p><p> “两名卖牛奶的妇女在这里被杀，”一名在炮击开始前几分钟离开市场的当地妇女说。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820302?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">莱曼周围地区是东线遭受俄罗斯炮击最严重的地区。 </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820303?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">俄罗斯军队瞄准了拥挤的地方，例如遭到火箭弹袭击的莱曼市场。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>乌克兰士兵表示，俄罗斯人最近开始瞄准商店和咖啡馆等拥挤的地方，那里是士兵与平民聚集的地方。莱曼炮击事件发生前大约一周，一枚俄罗斯导弹<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-victims-of-a-russian-strike-on-a-pizzeria-ukrainian-author-teenage-twins-ex-u-s-marine-94334447?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">摧毁了克拉马托尔斯克附近一家颇受欢迎的披萨店</a>，造成十几人死亡。</p><p>乌克兰士兵分布在顿巴斯地区工业中心以北的丘陵地区。他们常常驻扎在被主人废弃的简陋村屋里。</p><p>其中一位是亚历山大·亚布昌卡 (Oleksandr Yabchanka) 中尉，他是一名志愿战士、前儿科医生，在巴赫穆特的激烈战斗中受伤后正在康复中。当一架俄罗斯无人侦察机发现他和他的队友时，他和他的队友正试图营救一名受伤的士兵。迫击炮弹如雨点般落在他们身上，一名受伤的士兵变成了11岁，这表明俄罗斯已经追上了乌克兰早先在无人机方面的优势，并且可能已经超越了它。</p><p>亚布昌卡表示，乌克兰迫切需要更多能够探测和击落无人机的防空系统，例如“猎豹”（Gepard），这是一种德国制造的高射炮，配备雷达，安装在坦克底盘上。</p><p>他引用乌克兰工程师正在测试遥控炮塔的例子说，俄罗斯的入侵已经变成了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russian-turmoil-shows-a-forever-war-in-ukraine-hurts-putin-5cbb8738?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">一场消耗战</a>，乌克兰需要找到降低士兵风险的方法。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820307?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">亚历山大·亚布昌卡 (Oleksandr Yabchanka) 中尉是一名志愿战士，也是一名前儿科医生，最近受了轻伤，他在莱曼附近一个村庄的临时基地检查地图和无人机视频。 </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820322?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">乌克兰士兵经常驻扎在被主人废弃的简陋村屋里。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>他说：“俄罗斯人将尽可能长时间地战斗，我们也将尽可能长时间地战斗。”</p><p>在附近的另一个村庄，炮兵指挥官日塔尔回忆起俄罗斯人7月1日对莱曼进行的最后一次大规模进攻，部署了坦克、装甲运兵车、步兵和火炮试图突破。乌克兰人凭借大规模炮火成功阻止了他们。</p><p>日塔尔与另一名士兵和两只小猫住在一座废弃的村屋里。他在天篷的树荫下工作，桌子上放着几台收音机、一本记事本、几包香烟和几杯咖啡。</p><p>去年春天，当俄罗斯军队袭击基辅时，日塔尔从军事学院退学，担任“格沃兹迪卡”部队的指挥官。俄国人撤退后，他因战争而提早毕业，被派往东部，因为一枚俄国炮弹击中榴弹炮附近，他的一只耳朵已经听力受损。</p><p>在西北地区，俄罗斯人现在正在采用新的战术，在夜间派遣小股步兵在新阵地挖壕沟。 “他们的铲子很熟练，”他说。</p><p>但到目前为止，乌克兰军队仍坚守阵地。日塔尔表示，他的苏联时代“格沃兹迪卡”榴弹炮（名字翻译为“康乃馨”）非常准确。</p><p>在无线电中收到同一辆坦克再次试图前进的新报告后，日塔尔再次号召他的团队采取行动。</p><p>第一枪命中，他收到报告称，侦察无人机显示俄罗斯坦克冒出烟雾，表明受损。</p><p> “今天我们很幸运，”日塔尔说。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820318?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">俄罗斯的入侵已演变成一场消耗战，乌克兰则试图降低其士兵面临的风险。</p></figcaption></figure></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 21 Jul 2023 07:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ Russia-seeks-to-divert-ukrainian-forces-away-from-counteroffective-80580e89</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ Russia-seeks-to-divert-ukrainian-forces-away-from-counteroffective-80580e89<category>乌克兰</category><category>华尔街日报</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>武装部队</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>武装部队</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[U.S. Ambassador to China Hacked in China-Linked Spying Operation]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>间谍活动还损害了负责东亚事务的国务院官员的安全<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001071218"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821061?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">美国驻华大使尼古拉斯·伯恩斯本月早些时候在美国驻北京大使馆举行的气候金融圆桌讨论会上发表讲话。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：mark schiefelbein/pool/Shutterstock </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001071218"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/dustin-volz" itemprop="url" rel="author">达斯汀·沃尔兹 (Dustin Volz)</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/warren-p-strobel" itemprop="url" rel="author">沃伦·P·史特博 (Warren P. Strobel)</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 20 日下午 6:48（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-ambassador-to-china-hacked-in-china-linked-spying-operation-f03de3e4"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>据知情人士透露，与北京有关的黑客访问了美国驻华大使尼古拉斯·伯恩斯(Nicholas Burns)的电子邮件帐户，此次攻击据信已泄露了至少<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/microsoft-email-hack-shows-greater-sophistication-skill-of-chinas-cyberspies-7f7cff67?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">数十万封美国政府的个人电子邮件</a>。</p><p>知情人士称，负责东亚事务的助理国务卿丹尼尔·克里滕布林克(Daniel Kritenbrink)也在网络间谍攻击中遭到黑客攻击。其中一位知情人士称，这两名外交官据信是上周披露的涉嫌间谍活动的两名国务院最高官员。</p><p>该活动的轮廓尚不完全清楚。尽管仅限于非机密电子邮件，但伯恩斯和克里滕布林克的收件箱可能让黑客能够深入了解美国拜登政府高级官员最近一系列访华的计划，以及在近几个月来一再受到挑战的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-and-china-look-to-repair-ties-again-9e200b10?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">微妙外交时期</a>美国对其竞争对手政策的内部对话。</p><p>伯恩斯和克里滕布林克是新闻报道中第二位和第三位被确认电子邮件遭到黑客攻击的拜登政府高级官员。美国官员表示，商务部长吉娜·雷蒙多的电子邮件帐户<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-hackers-spied-on-state-department-13a09f03?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">也因此次泄露</a>而受到损害。</p><p>一位知情人士表示，国务卿安东尼·布林肯的电子邮件帐户及其高级顾问圈子的电子邮件帐户似乎并未在此次黑客攻击中直接渗透。相反，黑客似乎把重点放在了少数负责管理美中关系的高级官员身上。</p><p>知情人士表示，对个人电子邮件访问量的估计是粗略的，并且可能会增加。</p><p>美国国务院发言人表示：“出于安全原因，我们目前不会分享有关此次网络安全事件的性质和范围的更多信息。” “该部门持续监控并响应我们网络上值得关注的活动。我们的调查正在进行中，目前无法提供更多细节。”</p><p>白宫国家安全委员会拒绝置评。</p><p>一个月前，克里滕布林克陪同布林肯访华，克里滕布林克、伯恩斯和布林肯都出席了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/xi-jinping-to-meet-blinken-monday-as-u-s-china-resume-high-level-engagement-c898f541?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">与中国高级官员和中国领导人习近平的会晤</a>。在北京举行高层会谈之前，克里滕布林克率领较低级别官员进行了一次访问<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-and-china-prepare-for-possible-blinken-visit-to-beijing-2173d40d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，以奠定基础</a>。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821065?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">负责东亚事务的助理国务卿丹尼尔·克里滕布林克(Daniel Kritenbrink)在网络间谍攻击中遭到黑客攻击。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：韩联社/ZUMA Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>国务院领导拜登政府努力加强与中国的沟通，并在气候变化和合成阿片类药物贸易等特定领域取得进展。官员们表示<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/taiwan-elections-a-big-topic-during-blinkens-talks-in-china-afaa6def?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，在台湾、间谍和其他问题上根深蒂固的分歧</a>导致两国关系恶化，而美国对中国的广泛政治担忧阻止了这一趋势的逆转。</p><p>据该公司称，最近的黑客攻击是利用了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MSFT" class="">微软</a><span class="company-name-type">云</span>计算环境中的一个缺陷，该缺陷已得到修复，全球有超过两打组织受到影响。美国一位高级网络安全官员上周表示，美国只有不到 10 个组织受到攻击，而且每个组织似乎都拥有少量被黑客直接访问的个人电子邮件帐户。目前尚不清楚州和商务部以外的任何联邦机构是否成为攻击目标。</p><p>微软尚未公开披露此次泄露事件是如何开始的，并表示正在继续调查该事件。</p><p>美国官员将这次攻击描述为外科手术性质的攻击——针对少数专门选择的高价值受害者——并试图淡化其总体影响，将其比作敌对国家之间不断发生的常规数字间谍活动。</p><p>但安全专家和前情报官员表示，这次袭击似乎异乎寻常地隐蔽且令人印象深刻，并指出，此次袭击发生在美国和中国之间的外交关系有所加强之际，此前几个月， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-war-counteroffensive-frontlines-russia-add3e4e4?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">乌克兰战争</a>、美国发现并击落了所谓的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-spy-balloon-over-the-u-s-what-to-know-11675385792?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国监视气球</a>，以及<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/beijing-plans-a-new-training-facility-in-cuba-raising-prospect-of-chinese-troops-on-americas-doorstep-e17fd5d1" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国与古巴加强情报合作</a>的消息曝光，两国关系急剧恶化。</p><p>周四在阿斯彭安全论坛上被问及此次黑客攻击时，微软总裁布拉德·史密斯表示，这次网络攻击反映出黑客“日益成熟”，其目的是“从非机密电子邮件系统中提取信息”。</p><p>国家安全局网络安全主管罗布·乔伊斯（Rob Joyce）出现在史密斯旁边，他补充说，这次黑客攻击相当于美国政府一直面临的“相当传统的威胁”。</p><p> “这是中国在从事间谍活动，”乔伊斯说。 “这就是民族国家所做的事情。我们需要防御它，我们需要反击它，但这就是发生的事情。”</p><p>美国尚未正式将此次黑客攻击归咎于中国，但拜登政府高级官员表示，他们没有理由怀疑微软将其与中国黑客组织联系起来的评估。中国否认了这些指控，并指责美国在世界各地从事猖獗的网络间谍活动。</p><p>美国国务院的网络安全专家最先发现了间谍活动。微软表示，黑客攻击始于 5 月份，但直到 6 月中旬才被发现，这一日期与布林肯访华的时间非常吻合，布林肯是五年来第一位访问北京的美国国务卿。</p><p class="articleTagLine"> ——威廉·莫尔丁对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给达斯汀·沃尔兹 ( <a href="mailto:dustin.volz@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">dustin.volz@wsj.com)</a>和沃伦·P·史特博 (Warren P. Strobel) ( <a href="mailto:Warren.Strobel@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Warren.Strobel@wsj.com)</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 22:48:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-ambassador-to-china-hacked-in-china-linked-spying-operation-f03de3e4</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-ambassador-to-china-hacked-in-china-linked-spying-operation-f03de3e4<author><![CDATA[Dustin VolzWarren P. Strobel]]></author><category>专有的</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>隐私问题/信息安全</category><category>国际关系</category><category>网络犯罪/黑客攻击</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>数据安全漏洞</category><category>间谍</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>丹尼尔·克里滕布林克</category><category>尼古拉斯·伯恩斯</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>隐私问题</category><category>信息安全</category><category>国际关系</category><category>网络犯罪</category><category>黑客攻击</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category><category>数据安全漏洞</category><category>间谍</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ukrainian Military Warns Ships Against Heading to Russian Black Sea Ports]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>莫斯科发出类似警告，强调黑海对双方的战略重要性<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001070102"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820730?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">俄罗斯未能占领乌克兰南部海岸线黑海重要港口敖德萨。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：bo amstrup/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001070102"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jared-malsin" itemprop="url" rel="author">贾里德·马尔辛</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/matthew-luxmoore" itemprop="url" rel="author">马修·卢克斯摩尔</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 20 日下午 3:31（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukrainian-military-warns-ships-against-heading-to-russian-black-sea-ports-b309e287"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>俄罗斯和乌克兰都警告要袭击黑海的货船，这导致粮食运输争端升级，并有可能将战争扩大到战略航道。</p><p>乌克兰的声明于周四午夜生效，称所有驶往俄罗斯控制港口的船只都将“承担所有相关风险”。此外，乌克兰国防部表示，从周四凌晨 5 点开始，“乌克兰禁止在黑海东北部和将被占领的克里米亚与俄罗斯分隔开的刻赤海峡航行，因为这是危险的”。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/why-russia-killed-the-ukraine-grain-deal-faf1f8c5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">俄罗斯周三也发出了类似的威胁</a>，称将考虑任何前往乌克兰黑海港口的船只都可能携带军事物资，并试图禁止船只在国际水域的某些地区航行。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=AB99997C-BBCA-4660-BD78-5DE4B561FDBA&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fukrainian-military-warns-ships-against-heading-to-russian-black-sea-ports-b309e287&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">俄罗斯退出了一项允许乌克兰通过黑海出口粮食的国际协议。 《华尔街日报》的贾里德·马尔辛解释了这一决定背后的细节，以及这对全球粮食供应可能意味着什么。照片：Yoruk Isik/路透社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>乌克兰国防部表示：“俄罗斯联邦再次粗暴侵犯全世界自由航行的普遍权利，并蓄意破坏粮食安全，导致数百万人挨饿。”</p><p>在俄罗斯退出黑海粮食协议几天后，这些警告加深了黑海航运的不确定性。该协议允许乌克兰去年恢复大部分粮食出口，包括对中东和非洲市场的出口，自战争开始以来，这些地区<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/west-cant-afford-to-drop-the-ball-on-ukraine-u-k-foreign-secretary-says-95e6e5f8?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">的粮食供应一直是一个令人担忧的问题</a>。莫斯科撤军后的几个小时内，乌克兰军队开始对敖德萨港进行空中拦截，乌克兰军方官员称，这些拦截专门针对那里的重要基础设施。</p><p>白宫发言人奥利维亚·道尔顿周四表示，美国政府“已经看到迹象表明，俄罗斯基本上正在为可能袭击通过黑海运送谷物的民用船只做好准备”。</p><p>国家安全委员会发言人约翰·柯比表示，美国最新的情报估计还表明，俄罗斯正在考虑在通往乌克兰港口的航道上放置更多的水雷，以进行潜在的假旗行动。柯比对记者表示：“我们认为，这是一次协调一致的努力，目的是为黑海针对民用船只的任何袭击辩护，然后将其归咎于乌克兰。”</p><p>俄罗斯 2022 年 2 月的入侵最初导致乌克兰黑海出口中断，对该国港口实施了事实上的封锁，而战前该国港口占该国农产品出口的 95%。自俄罗斯本周退出谷物协议以来，该国主要黑海港口的出口再次大幅下降。</p><p>现在，乌克兰正试图限制俄罗斯黑海港口的交通，阻碍莫斯科自己的出口，就像俄罗斯试图拒绝进入乌克兰港口一样。</p><p>乌克兰总统泽连斯基的顾问米哈伊洛·波多利亚克在谈到俄罗斯时表示，“从其目前撕毁协议和袭击敖德萨港口基础设施的行为来看，它正试图在黑海占据主导地位。”</p><p>他说，乌克兰的警告旨在表明，如果俄罗斯违反国际法，乌克兰应该有权反击，甚至使用西方提供的武器攻击俄罗斯领土上的目标——但现在乌克兰不能这样做。</p><p>波多利亚克在接受采访时表示：“这不是镜像反应。”他补充说，敖德萨周围的防空系统一直难以拦截俄罗斯导弹。</p><p>军事分析人士表示，乌克兰不太可能真正袭击俄罗斯货船，因为它的反舰导弹供应有限。它还面临着收集超出其控制区域的目标数据的能力的限制。</p><p>尽管如此，乌克兰的最后通牒可能会导致保险公司停止为前往该地区的船只提供保险，从而阻止一些往返俄罗斯的航运。</p><p>美国海军战争学院俄罗斯海事研究所所长迈克尔·彼得森表示：“乌克兰正试图通过对俄罗斯实施保险封锁来扭转局面。”</p><p>自从入侵乌克兰后受到西方制裁以来，俄罗斯已转向依靠老化油轮和其他船只组成的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-will-rely-on-shadow-tanker-fleet-to-keep-oil-flowing-11670036535" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">影子舰队</a>来维持其石油出口。其黑海港口对其经济来说越来越重要，运输谷物、石油和其他商品。仅新罗西斯克港就占俄罗斯海上贸易的17%。</p><p>乌克兰使用鱼叉和海王星反舰导弹以及武装无人机击沉了俄罗斯军舰，并将俄罗斯海军从敖德萨市周围水域赶了回来。据《华尔街日报》 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sanctioned-russian-cargo-ships-made-more-than-100-stops-at-turkish-ports-e6b723c3?st=jdr37j3xrlqd17u&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">此前报道</a>，俄罗斯在战争期间转向其民用货船队运输武器。</p><p>乌克兰还使用海上无人机造成了毁灭性的影响。周一，连接俄罗斯和被占领克里米亚半岛的桥梁发生爆炸，外界普遍认为这是乌克兰所为。</p><p> “我只是不相信乌克兰有足够的资金对俄罗斯船只实施某种严格的封锁。货船太多了。俄罗斯人的安全措施太多，而乌克兰人的海上资源太少。”彼得森说。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820728?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">上个月，乌克兰谷物在罗马尼亚康斯坦察港卸货，随后俄罗斯退出了一项允许其出口的协议。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Vadim Ghirda/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>俄罗斯长期以来一直寻求扩大其在黑海地区的势力，利用其帝国历史的记忆，俄罗斯于 1783 年首次将黑海舰队总部驻扎在克里米亚的塞瓦斯托波尔。俄罗斯于 2014 年占领并吞并了克里米亚，当时俄罗斯在乌克兰南部和东部开始了低级别战争。</p><p>自2022年入侵以来，乌克兰南部海岸线，包括其黑海港口，一直是俄罗斯的战略目标，在乌克兰军队将俄罗斯军队从尼古拉耶夫市击退后，俄罗斯未能占领敖德萨和其他主要城市。</p><p>乌克兰还挫败了俄罗斯控制该航道的企图，去年击沉了俄罗斯黑海舰队的旗舰以及其他几艘俄罗斯船只。 2022 年 6 月，乌克兰军队还把俄罗斯军队赶出了面积虽小但具有战略意义的蛇岛。</p><p>去年7月，俄罗斯和乌克兰签署了由土耳其和联合国斡旋的《黑海粮食倡议》。该协议使乌克兰能够出口超过3200万吨玉米、小麦、葵花籽油和其他商品。该协议包括对两国的安全保证，所有参与该协议的船只在伊斯坦布尔进出黑海时都要接受检查。</p><p>俄罗斯周一暂停参与该协议，称其希望联合国遵守去年签署的另一项协议，该协议要求降低本国食品和化肥出口壁垒。</p><p>乌克兰呼吁与土耳其和联合国建立伙伴关系，以确保黑海粮食交易在没有俄罗斯参与的情况下继续进行。其官员表示，俄罗斯对该地区航运的威胁是对乌克兰努力寻找可能的解决办法以允许粮食运输继续进行的回应。</p><p>乌克兰总统顾问波多利亚克表示，乌克兰正在采取外交努力以继续粮食出口，其与土耳其和联合国的讨论包括寻找替代路线等选择。他说，基辅还正在推动由配备适当防空系统的西方军舰（护卫舰或驱逐舰等船只）保护的车队，以允许粮食运输继续进行。</p><p class="articleTagLine"> ——华盛顿的安妮·林斯基对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给 Jared Malsin： <a href="mailto:jared.malsin@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">jared.malsin@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 19:31:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukrainian-military-warns-ships-against-heading-to- Russian-black-sea-ports-b309e287</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukrainian-military-warns-ships-against-heading-to- Russian-black-sea-ports-b309e287<author><![CDATA[Jared MalsinMatthew Luxmoore]]></author><category>乌克兰</category><category>华尔街日报</category><category>海运</category><category>水路运输/航运</category><category>运输/物流</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>海运</category><category>水运</category><category>船运</category><category>运输</category><category>后勤</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Iraq Expels Swedish Ambassador Amid Protests Over Quran Desecration]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>听说瑞典允许焚烧伊斯兰教的神圣文本后，人群纵火焚烧驻巴格达大使馆<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001069512"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=60B96BB5-D1B4-4ED6-8F76-7CD927DBFA17&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fswedish-embassy-in-iraq-set-on-fire-in-protest-against-planned-quran-burning-ed731d20&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">周四，在人群纵火焚烧瑞典驻巴格达大使馆以抗议斯德哥尔摩计划焚烧《古兰经》几小时后，伊拉克政府驱逐了瑞典大使。瑞典谴责大使馆袭击事件是不可接受的。照片：Ahmad Al-Rubaye/法新社/盖蒂图片社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001069512"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/sune-engel-rasmussen" itemprop="url" rel="author">苏尼·恩格尔·拉斯穆森</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name">加桑·阿德南</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 20 日下午 3:00（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/swedish-embassy-in-iraq-set-on-fire-in-protest-against-planned-quran-burning-ed731d20"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>巴格达——周四，伊拉克驱逐了瑞典大使，几小时前，愤怒的伊拉克人冲进了位于巴格达市中心的瑞典大使馆，翻墙并纵火焚烧，以抗议斯德哥尔摩可能公开亵渎《古兰经》。</p><p>伊拉克还召回了驻斯德哥尔摩的临时代办，政府暂停了瑞典电信公司<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/ERIC" class="company-name">爱立信</a>在该国的运营许可。伊拉克什叶派民兵阿沙布·卡夫呼吁其支持者攻击瑞典在伊拉克的利益。</p><p>伊拉克总理穆罕默德·苏达尼谴责大使馆袭击事件，但批评瑞典以言论自由为借口允许焚烧《古兰经》，称国际准则强调尊重宗教。苏丹尼说：“此类行为被视为对和平的威胁，并鼓励暴力和仇恨文化。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820535?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">周四，穆克塔达·萨德尔的支持者在瑞典驻巴格达大使馆举行抗议活动时举着什叶派神职人员的照片。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：ahmad al-rubaye/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>伊拉克政府表示，瑞典政府一再允许焚烧《古兰经》、侮辱伊斯兰神圣性和焚烧伊拉克国旗，促使其采取外交行动。社交媒体上分享的视频显示，周四早些时候，民粹主义什叶派穆斯林神职人员萨德尔的数百名追随者在瑞典大使馆聚集，其中一些人在凌晨 2 点左右进入了大使馆。安全部队黎明后抵达后，抗议者撤离了大院，但他们继续在外面示威。</p><p>瑞典外交部表示，其所有工作人员均安全。瑞典和共用该建筑的芬兰大使馆也撤离了人员。</p><p>周四，瑞典警方批准了在伊拉克驻斯德哥尔摩大使馆外举行示威的申请，瑞典媒体称，两名抗议者将焚烧《古兰经》和伊拉克国旗，这可能是为了回应上个月在巴格达发生的反瑞典抗议活动，随后伊拉克爆发了抗议活动。</p><p>根据社交媒体上分享的视频，巴格达抗议活动结束后，瑞典发生了一场示威活动，一名示威者将一本《古兰经》踢向空中，但没有焚烧它。抗议活动似乎吸引了很少的观众。</p><p>几个月来，瑞典对焚烧《古兰经》的容忍一直是中东地区的一个热点问题，土耳其则以此为手段<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/turkeys-erdogan-threatens-to-block-swedens-nato-entrance-over-quran-burning-11674498389?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，阻碍斯德哥尔摩申请</a>加入北大西洋公约组织。瑞典政府谴责<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sweden-arrests-dozens-in-clashes-over-far-right-leaders-plan-to-burn-quran-11650306872?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">焚烧《古兰经》</a>是反穆斯林的挑衅行为，但表示该国拥有影响深远的言论自由。</p><p>瑞典外交部长托比亚斯·比尔斯特罗姆周四表示：“亵渎《古兰经》或任何其他圣经都是一种冒犯性和不尊重的行为，也是一种明显的挑衅。” “瑞典政府对极端分子和煽动者试图在穆斯林和非穆斯林之间制造分裂感到非常遗憾。”</p><p>其他穆斯林国家对瑞典允许焚烧古兰经等抗议活动表示愤怒。伊朗表示，由于神圣文本被毁，它将不会任命驻瑞典大使。沙特阿拉伯、埃及和马来西亚都谴责焚烧古兰经是针对伊斯兰教的仇恨行为。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820533?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">周四，伊拉克防暴警察对瑞典大使馆的抗议活动做出了回应。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：ahmad al-rubaye/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>联合国驻伊拉克使团谴责了大使馆袭击事件，但也将焚烧《古兰经》称为“仇恨言论”——而瑞典则不然——称用暴力对抗对任何人都没有帮助。</p><p>在瑞典，当仇恨言论基于种族、民族、性取向或信仰威胁或不尊重团体或个人时，仇恨言论就会被定为刑事犯罪，但焚烧《古兰经》被视为对该国法律保护的宗教的批评。</p><p>美国国务院发言人马修·米勒表示，伊拉克安全部队没有阻止这次袭击是不可接受的。</p><p>米勒说：“和平集会自由是民主的重要标志，但昨晚发生的事情是非法的暴力行为。”</p><p>比尔斯特罗姆谴责大使馆袭击事件是完全不可接受的。 “伊拉克当局有明确的义务保护外交使团和外交人员，”他说。 “很明显，伊拉克当局严重未能履行这一责任。”</p><p>比尔斯特罗姆说，瑞典政府已召集伊拉克驻斯德哥尔摩临时代办“审查需要采取哪些进一步措施”。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="525" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820539?width=700&amp;height=525" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">周四是近几周来抗议者第二次闯入瑞典驻巴格达大使馆大院。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：ammar karim/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>苏丹尼办公室表示，总理已召集伊拉克外交部长、内政部长以及安全负责人讨论这一事件。声明称，一些肇事者已被逮捕并将受到起诉，玩忽职守的安全人员将受到讯问。</p><p>大使馆袭击事件发生后，萨德尔表示瑞典允许焚烧国旗违反了所有外交准则，并指责瑞典是伊斯兰教的敌人。</p><p>周四对瑞典驻巴格达大使馆的袭击是不到一个月内的第二次袭击，六月下旬，斯德哥尔摩一座清真寺外焚烧《古兰经》，数千名萨德尔追随者在大使馆抗议。一些抗议者进入了大院，其他人高呼支持萨德尔的口号，并焚烧彩虹色的旗帜，这显然是对 LGBTQ 群体的侮辱。</p><p>尽管所有伊拉克政党都支持政府驱逐瑞典最高外交官的决定，但苏丹的一些盟友担心，萨德尔煽动巴格达抗议活动的目标之一是通过强调政府无力维护安全来削弱政府。</p><p> 2022 年 7 月，在萨德尔及其盟友在去年 10 月的选举胜利后证明无法组建政府后，数百名萨德尔的追随者袭击了伊拉克议会大楼，以类似的方式展示力量。萨德尔在骚乱后宣布退出政坛，但自苏丹尼十月上任以来一直在寻找重新行使权力的方法。</p><p>瑞典的《古兰经》抗议活动最初似乎是为了阻止<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sweden-races-to-secure-turkish-support-for-nato-bid-2452c14f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">该国加入北约的申请</a>，但只吸引了极少数人参与。</p><p>今年早些时候，瑞典警方拒绝了几项包括焚烧《古兰经》在内的抗议申请。法院后来推翻了警方的决定，认为拒绝与该国的言论自由法相冲突。</p><p>爱立信发言人表示，该公司在伊拉克拥有约 30 名全职员工，正在调查当地有关其工作许可证被吊销的报道。她补充说，瑞典发生的亵渎《古兰经》事件并没有反映出该公司尊重的核心价值观。</p><p class="articleTagLine"> —David S. Cloud 对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给 Sune Engel Rasmussen： <a href="mailto:sune.rasmussen@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">sune.rasmussen@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 19:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/swedish-embassy-in-iraq-set-on-fire-in-protest-against-planned-quran-burning-ed731d20</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/swedish-embassy-in-iraq-set-on-fire-in-protest-against-planned-quran-burning-ed731d20<author><![CDATA[Sune Engel Rasmussen]]></author><category>华尔街日报</category><category>电信设备</category><category>技术</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>内乱</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>国际关系</category><category>人权/公民自由</category><category>伊斯兰教</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>宗教</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>社会问题</category><category>军事行动</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Telefon AB LM 爱立信 B 系列</category><category>ERIC-B.SK</category><category> SE：ERIC.B</category><category>爱立信</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>内乱</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>国际关系</category><category>人权</category><category>公民权利</category><category>伊斯兰教</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category><category>宗教</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>社会问题</category><category>军事行动</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>电信设备</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[France’s Macron Shuffles His Government, Seeking a Fresh Start]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>在近几个月的抗议浪潮之后，法国领导人正在寻求恢复他的第二个任期<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001070953"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820542?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">法国总统埃马纽埃尔·马克龙(Emmanuel Macron)将八名部长从内阁中撤职。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：约翰娜·杰隆/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001070953"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/noemie-bisserbe" itemprop="url" rel="author">诺埃米·比瑟布</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 20 日下午 2:33 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/frances-macron-shuffles-his-government-seeking-a-fresh-start-b76a77ec"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>巴黎——在震惊全国的数月抗议和骚乱之后，总统埃马纽埃尔·马克龙正在对法国政府进行重组，以帮助恢复他的第二个任期。</p><p>在周四宣布的内阁改组中，八名部长被免职，此举旨在重塑一个笨拙的政府，该政府<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/macrons-parliamentary-majority-at-risk-in-final-round-of-french-elections-11655631002?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">在马克龙去年失去国民议会多数席位</a>后一直难以治理国家。但官员们表示，他没有进行大规模改革——至少目前是这样——让伊丽莎白·博尔恩总理继续留任，他也曾考虑过解雇她。</p><p>经过数月的危机后，马克龙的新内阁面临着重新调整政治议程的挑战。本月早些时候，在一名青少年被警察<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/riots-erupt-in-paris-suburbs-after-police-kill-teenager-acf46a38" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">枪杀</a>后， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/french-riots-escalate-as-macron-struggles-to-respond-2ebbd315" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">骚乱者连续一周每天晚上都走上街头</a>，焚烧汽车、烧毁建筑物并抢劫商店，从马赛到巴黎。</p><p>就在这场暴力事件爆发的几周前，政府在今年春天努力遏制因马克龙<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/french-pension-strikes-retirement-age-reform-macron-ce377388?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">不受欢迎的提高退休年龄决定</a>而<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/french-protests-grow-volatile-in-test-for-macron-3bec9003?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">引发的抗议</a>之后，终于恢复了相对平静。</p><p>马克龙去年再次当选总统，成为自2002年以来首位连任的法国总统。他的亲商业政党复兴党在法国下议院拥有最多席位，但该党不再拥有压倒性多数席位，无法让法国领导人在第一个任期内压倒反对派。</p><p>今年3月，马克龙政府援引宪法特殊权力，绕过议会，将国家退休年龄从62岁提高到64岁。此举引发全国各地的暴力抗议。几天后，政府在国民议会的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/macrons-government-survives-no-confidence-vote-in-frances-national-assembly-52126b56" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">不信任投票中险胜</a>。</p><p> 6月下旬，17岁的北非裔男子纳赫尔·梅尔祖克(Nahel Merzouk)在巴黎郊区的一个交通站点被警察开枪射击，此后，马克龙面临着新的危机。一名目击者拍摄的杀人视频显示，一名警察用手枪指着驾驶员侧的车窗，这引发了法国民众的愤怒，重新引发了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/behind-french-riots-lie-years-of-anger-over-police-conduct-95df6c4d" target="_blank" class="icon none">关于警察暴力和种族定性的辩论</a>。</p><p>马克龙迅速谴责梅尔祖克被杀是不可原谅的，法国检察官对这名警官提出了故意杀人的初步指控。这还不足以平息数千名骚乱者的愤怒，他们走上巴黎和其他法国城市的街头。内政部长杰拉尔德·达尔马宁 (Gérald Darmanin) 在全国部署了约 45,000 名警察来制止暴力，暴力最终平息。</p><p>达马宁周四保留了他的职位。但在这次洗牌中，马克龙用预算部长加布里埃尔·阿塔尔取代了教育部长。他还空降博恩的幕僚长奥雷利安·卢梭（Aurélien Rousseau）担任新任卫生部长。</p><p>负责监管非营利部门的副部长玛琳·斯基亚帕 (Marlène Schiappa) 也被赶下台，她曾因她在 2021 年发起的公共基金的管理问题而受到调查。她最近还因接受《花花公子》采访时摆出穿着服装的照片而成为头条新闻。</p><p>写信给 Noemie Bisserbe，邮箱为<a href="mailto:noemie.bisserbe@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">noemie.bisserbe@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 18:33:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/frances-macron-shuffles-his-government-seeking-a-fresh-start-b76a77ec</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/frances-macron-shuffles-his-government-seeking-a-fresh-start-b76a77ec<author><![CDATA[Noemie Bisserbe]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>内乱</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>社会问题</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>伊曼纽尔·马克龙</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>内乱</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>社会问题</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[How Trump Ended Up With Israeli Antiquities]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>在以色列呼吁后，前总统同意归还陶瓷油灯和硬币<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001068998"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="860" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820470?width=860&amp;height=860" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">以色列文物管理局提供的文物在海湖庄园赠送给唐纳德·特朗普。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：索尔·福克斯</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001068998"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/alex-leary" itemprop="url" rel="author">亚历克斯·利里 (Alex Leary)</a></span> 、 <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/dov-lieber" itemprop="url" rel="author">多夫·利伯 (Dov Lieber</a></span> ) 和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/annie-linskey" itemprop="url" rel="author">安妮·林斯基 (Annie Linskey)</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 20 日下午 1:47（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-donald-trump-ended-up-with-priceless-israeli-antiquities-74d9e037"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>在以色列文物当局发起一场公开运动要求归还古代文物后，前总统<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/donald-trump">唐纳德·特朗普</a>同意归还这些文物。</p><p>作为以色列国宝收藏的一部分的陶瓷油灯如何最终落入特朗普的海湖庄园的故事很复杂。在这段传奇故事中，这些文物差点就造访了白宫，在加州的一个壁橱里存放了几个月，然后在佛罗里达州通过 X 光机检查，然后才交付给特朗普。</p><p>特朗普发言人周三表示：“这些历史物品是由以色列文物管理局的代表在该组织的全力支持下展示的。”他补充说，这些物品是租借用于永久展览的。 “由于这些物品按照最初的预期展示，该办公室将加快将其返还给该组织的代表，”他说。</p><p>他们的现代旅程开始于 2019 年，当时私募股权高管、共和党的长期捐助者和以色列的支持者索尔·福克斯 (Saul Fox) 接到时任以色列文物管理局局长伊斯雷尔·哈森 (Israel Hasson) 的电话，称他要来美国并希望与他会面。福克斯刚刚受邀参加白宫的光明节派对，并建议向特朗普赠送来自耶路撒冷的古董，以纪念他对以色列的支持。</p><p>哈森在接受采访时表示，哈森带着黑色新秀丽随身行李前往福克斯在加利福尼亚州的家，里面装着一系列无价的灯具和硬币，这些物品原本打算在白宫暂时展示几周，然后返回。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819286?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">来自以色列的文物于 2021 年底被带到海湖庄园度假村。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：giorgio viera/法新社/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>新秀丽包里的物品接下来到达了华盛顿，但没有到达白宫。</p><p>福克斯在接受采访时表示，国务院想要检查它们，但没有及时归还光明节庆祝活动。 “我有点尴尬，”他说。几名国务院官员周三表示，他们不记得这次遭遇。</p><p>大约三个月后，福克斯聘请了一名快递员前往华盛顿取回这些物品，并支付了额外的飞机座位费用，以便将它们放在快递员身边。在加利福尼亚州的家中，福克斯把包锁起来，“然后就忘记了它”。</p><p>然后新冠疫情袭来，世界陷入封锁，以色列的返回时间被推迟。</p><p> 2021年底，福克斯收到邀请参加海湖庄园烛光晚宴，当时正值光明节期间。</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> “有一个意第绪语单词‘bashert’——意思是天生的，”福克斯说。</p><p>他再次联系了哈森，后者已不再担任文物管理局的职务。 “这又是一个恶棍，”福克斯说。 “他告诉我，‘索尔，我明天碰巧要和新导演开早餐会，我会问他。’在与福克斯和导演伊莱·埃斯科西多（Eli Eskosido）进行 Zoom 通话后，制定了将这些物品交给特朗普的计划。福克斯的女朋友制作了一个黑色展示盒。一张卡片解释了这些物品并规定它们是借用的。</p><p>他们从加利福尼亚州出发前往佛罗里达州。特勤局坚持将盒子带到 X 光机处。最后，福克斯带着盒子进入了海湖庄园，并在他的办公室见到了特朗普。几分钟后，这位前总统站起来说他得准备吃晚饭了。</p><p> “我挡住了他的路，说道：‘先生。总统，不，不，你不能离开，我有我写的这些话，”福克斯告诉他。他宣读了准备好的讲话，赞扬特朗普对以色列的立场，包括将美国大使馆迁至耶路撒冷。福克斯说，特朗普把手拍在桌子上，并咆哮道：“好吧，为什么我只得到了 25% 的犹太人选票？”</p><p> “我迅速想了想，说道：‘先生。总统先生，我知道您对里诺人（名义上的共和党人）有问题，我们美国的犹太人对基诺人（名义上的犹太人）有问题，比如亚当·希夫（Adam Schiff）和</p>查克·舒默（Chuck Schumer），指的是来自纽约的加州民主党众议院议员和参议院多数党领袖。<p></p><p> “是的，没错，”特朗普说。 “非常好。现在走吧。”晚餐时，福克斯和他的女朋友与特朗普和他的妻子梅拉尼娅坐在一张桌子旁。 “这很漂亮，”他说。</p><p>倒回一点。</p><p>福克斯说，当他收到一封来自埃斯科西多的电子邮件时，他正坐在海湖庄园的大厅里：“他说存在某种沟通不畅。你必须立即将这些带回以色列。” <strong>&nbsp;</strong>福克斯问他在科技行业工作的女朋友，如果他读了这封电子邮件，是否有人会知道。是的，她说，但他决定继续前进。</p><p>他对特朗普说：“为纪念您而在以色列国境外永久展览以色列国宝，这是史无前例的。”福克斯在接受采访时表示，该协议从未规定这些物品的归还日期。福克斯说，它们不是特朗普的，但他实际上将充当它们的保管人。</p><p>他说，几个月后，他接到一名美国男子的电话，重申以色列希望归还这些物品。福克斯表示，这样做是一种冒犯。福克斯说：“这是我承诺并做到的事情，我真诚地履行了这一承诺。”</p><p>福克斯说，直到本周他才再次听到任何消息，当时朋友们开始向他发送有关以色列文物当局如何寻找这些文物的文章副本，以色列报纸《国土报》早些时候报道了这一努力。</p><p>负责 2019 年最初安排谈判的哈森表示，“索尔·福克斯与古物管理局的合作是透明的。”</p><p class="articleTagLine"> ——维维安·萨拉马对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给 Alex Leary ( <a href="mailto:alex.leary@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">alex.leary@wsj.com)</a> 、Dov Lieber ( <a href="mailto:dov.lieber@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">dov.lieber@wsj.com</a> ) 和 Annie Linskey ( <a href="mailto:annie.linskey@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">annie.linskey@wsj.com</a> )</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 17:47:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-donald-trump-ending-up-with-priceless-israeli-antiquities-74d9e037</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-donald-trump-ending-up-with-priceless-israeli-antiquities-74d9e037<author><![CDATA[Alex LearyDov LieberAnnie Linskey]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>商品市场</category><category>能源市场</category><category>商品/金融市场新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 排除过滤器</category><category>IWE过滤器</category><category>日常市场/财经新闻</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>索尔·福克斯</category><category>唐纳德·特朗普</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>商品市场</category><category>能源市场</category><category>商品</category><category>金融市场新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e 排除过滤器</category><category>伊威过滤器</category><category>常规市场</category><category>财经新闻</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Xi Jinping Praises Henry Kissinger in Beijing]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> China&#39;s leader skipped a meeting with John Kerry, the other former US secretary of state in Beijing this week <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001069506"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820543?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> China&#39;s President Xi Jinping hosted former US Secretary of State Henry Kissinger this week in Beijing.</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：-/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001069506"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/joyu-wang" itemprop="url" rel="author">Joyu Wang</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Updated July 20, 2023 7:46 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/xi-jinping-praises-henry-kissinger-in-beijing-in-veiled-message-to-biden-administration-f305e878"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> TAIPEI—Beijing&#39;s warm embrace of Henry Kissinger this week sent a pointed signal to the Biden administration: Stop trying to contain us.</p><p> On Thursday, Chinese leader Xi Jinping welcomed Richard Nixon&#39;s secretary of state to Beijing&#39;s Diaoyutai State Guesthouse, lavishing gratitude on the 100-year-old for his role in <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/what-i-learned-from-henry-kissinger-74f21e53?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">normalizing diplomatic relations</a> between the US and China half a century ago.</p><p> Video footage from China&#39;s state broadcaster showed the pair meeting in the same building where, in July 1971, Kissinger first met China&#39;s then-Premier Zhou Enlai for secret talks to discuss re-establishing diplomatic ties. With sentimental piano music playing in the background, Xi praised the “splendid strategic vision” of that past diplomatic effort, adding: “We&#39;ll never forget our old friend.”</p><p> Kissinger&#39;s reception in Beijing, which included a meeting with China&#39;s defense minister who snubbed his <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-defense-chief-austin-rebukes-china-for-being-unwilling-to-engage-28cabd8c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">current American counterpart</a> earlier this summer, was markedly different from that of the White House&#39;s climate envoy John Kerry, who was <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-sets-heat-record-as-john-kerry-arrives-to-discuss-climate-6a35c686?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">seeking to revive cooperation</a> on climate change. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=AEFDD20E-B8EC-4F14-B1AA-8439E0D73B67&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fxi-jinping-praises-henry-kissinger-in-beijing-in-veiled-message-to-biden-administration-f305e878&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">总统气候特使约翰·克里在此次访问中会见了中国总理李强，旨在试图重振陷入僵局的气候变化合作。照片：Florence Lo/路透社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>Kerry, himself a former secretary of state under Barack Obama, was, like Kissinger, described by senior Chinese officials as “an old friend.” Unlike Kissinger, he didn&#39;t get a meeting with Xi.</p><p> Instead, the Chinese leader attended a separate forum on climate change, where he said that China would pursue <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/kerrys-china-trip-restores-talks-on-climate-change-but-falls-short-on-agreement-f89be8e2?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">its own climate goals</a> “free from outside interference.”</p><p> “We were aware that Henry Kissinger was traveling to China,” State Department spokesman Matthew Miller told a press briefing on Tuesday. “He was there under his own volition, not acting on behalf of the United States government.”</p><p> The Kissinger trip, and its contrast with Kerry&#39;s sojourn, highlights the two-pronged approach that Beijing has taken when it comes to repairing badly fractured ties with the US While accepting Washington&#39;s entreaties to re-engage, it is pushing to do so on its own terms, with Americans that it regards as trustworthy. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="463" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820708?width=700&amp;height=463" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Henry Kissinger at a meeting with a top Chinese official in Beijing in 2019.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Jason Lee/REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> In June, as the US and China were gearing up to revive high-level contacts cut off after President Biden ordered a suspected Chinese spy balloon shot down, Xi met in Beijing with <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MSFT" class="company-name">Microsoft</a> founder Bill Gates.</p> Xi told Gates, whose company has a long history in China, that he was the <a href="https://www.wsj.com/video/chinas-xi-jinping-meets-old-friend-bill-gates-in-beijing/70598DF6-8CEE-46C1-9CB8-E2E94FCFBE86.html?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">first American he had seen that year</a> . A Chinese official said Xi, who would <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/xi-jinping-to-meet-blinken-monday-as-u-s-china-resume-high-level-engagement-c898f541?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">meet with Secretary of State Antony Blinken</a> days later, wanted to ensure he met with a friendlier American beforehand.<p></p><p> During Thursday&#39;s meeting with Kissinger at Diaoyutai&#39;s Villa No. 5, Xi said relations between the US and China had—five decades after Kissinger&#39;s first visit—once again reached a crossroads.</p><p> “I hope you and other insightful Americans will continue to play a constructive role in bringing US-China relations back on the right track,” Xi told his guest.</p><p> According to a Chinese state-media account, Kissinger emphasized the importance to Beijing of what it calls the “one China principle,” referring to Beijing&#39;s claim over democratically self-ruled Taiwan—and indirectly rebuking the Biden administration for tightening ties with the government in Taipei. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820544?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> John Kerry spent four days in Beijing this week as the White House&#39;s climate envoy.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Andy Wong/Associated Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Potentially more consequential was Kissinger&#39;s meeting on Tuesday with Li Shangfu, China&#39;s defense minister. The meeting came roughly a month after Li <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-rebuffs-pentagon-chief-blunting-push-for-rapprochement-dd78d9bf" target="_blank" class="icon none">bluntly declined a meeting</a> with US Defense Secretary Lloyd Austin at an annual security forum in Singapore, despite a US push to improve military-to-military communication with China.</p><p> The US has argued that better communication is necessary to avoid a catastrophic misunderstanding between the militaries. China has dismissed the request as insincere. It also pointed to sanctions the US <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-rolls-out-new-guidelines-on-russia-sanctions-policy-1537463788" target="_blank" class="icon none">has</a> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-rolls-out-new-guidelines-on-russia-sanctions-policy-1537463788?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">imposed on Li</a> since 2018 when he ran the Chinese military&#39;s armaments departments and purchased combat aircraft and missile equipment from Russia.</p><p> In his meeting with Kissinger, Li said “some people in the United States did not meet China halfway, causing China-US relations to hover at the lowest point since the establishment of diplomatic relations,” according to a readout from China&#39;s Defense Ministry. He called on Washington to adopt the “correct strategic judgment,” saying he still held out hope for improved relations.</p><p> For his part, Kissinger urged the two militaries <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/henry-kissinger-is-worried-about-disequilibrium-11660325251" target="_blank" class="icon none">to strengthen communication</a> , according to the Chinese readout. “Neither the US nor China could afford seeing each other as a rival,” it quoted him as saying. “If the two countries go to war, it will not bring any meaningful results for their people.”</p><p> Miller, the State Department spokesman, said Kissinger&#39;s meeting with Li didn&#39;t violate the US sanctions, just as Lloyd would have also been free to meet with the Chinese defense minister had he been willing.</p><p> During his trip, Kissinger also met Wang Yi, China&#39;s top foreign-affairs official, who on Wednesday praised the former Secretary of State by saying: “The US&#39;s China policy requires the diplomatic wisdom of Kissinger and the political courage of Nixon.”</p><p> Write to Joyu Wang at <a href="mailto:joyu.wang@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">joyu.wang@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 11:46:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/xi-jinping-praises-henry-kissinger-in-beijing-in-veiled-message-to-biden-administration-f305e878</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/xi-jinping-praises-henry-kissinger-in-beijing-in-veiled-message-to-biden-administration-f305e878<author><![CDATA[Joyu Wang]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>亨利·基辛格</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[This Arkansas Town Could Become the Epicenter of a U.S. Lithium Boom]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Companies such as Exxon Mobil plan to extract lithium from brine water to help power electric vehicles <figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819556/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="An influx of workers and trucks could give Magnolia, Ark., and nearby counties an economic boost after years of decline." referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption> An influx of workers and trucks could give Magnolia, Ark., and nearby counties an economic boost after years of decline. <span></span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001067627"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001067627"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/collin-eaton" itemprop="url" rel="author">Collin Eaton</a></span> and <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/benoit-morenne" itemprop="url" rel="author">Benoît Morenne</a></span> | Photographs by David Yerby for The Wall Street Journal</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 20, 2023 7:00 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/this-arkansas-town-could-become-the-epicenter-of-a-u-s-lithium-boom-54ad7306"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p> MAGNOLIA, Ark.—Slipping a handgun into his belt, the mayor of this small town hopped out of his 1995 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/F" class="company-name">Ford</a> pickup and went in search of further evidence of a new energy boom.</p><p> On the other side of a freshly painted gate, Mayor Parnell Vann pointed out a squat blue spire of valves, bolts and pressure gauges attached to a long-dormant well—a telltale sign someone means to bring it back to life. On the thick-wooded back roads, crisscrossing fields where oil drillers gave up long ago, Vann found two more similar wells that day.</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> These days, companies in the area aren&#39;t looking to find more oil—they are instead prospecting for lithium, a metal that is increasingly prized around the world as an <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-surprising-new-source-of-lithium-for-batteries-744463c4?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">essential ingredient in electric-vehicle batteries</a> .</p><p> If the US is to ease its dependence for lithium on other countries such as China, it may need this quiet corner of southwest Arkansas to lead the way.</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/XOM" class="">Exxon Mobil</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span> a new player in the hunt for US lithium, is planning to build one of the world&#39;s largest lithium processing facilities not far from Magnolia, with a capacity to produce 75,000 to 100,000 metric tons of lithium a year, according to people familiar with the matter.</p><p> At that scale, it would equate to about 15% of all finished lithium produced globally last year, according to one analyst. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><img width="600" height="1156" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/77030763-5dd2-4be4-accf-f1b9cb891fc2-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> The Wall Street Journal reported in May that <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/exxon-joins-hunt-for-lithium-in-bet-on-ev-boom-1d72cdd6?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Exxon purchased 120,000 gross acres</a> in the area for a price tag of more than $100 million. A consultant for the seller had estimated the prospect could have the equivalent of 4 million tons of lithium carbonate equivalent, enough to power 50 million EVs.</p><p> The giant project could be built in stages, with modular trains constructed together or in separate locations near its future lithium production sites in South Arkansas, people familiar with the matter said.</p><p> To push the project forward, Exxon will have to profitably scale up the technology used to siphon lithium from brine, which for years has been an elusive goal across the industry.</p><p> Other companies including <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/CA/XTSX/SLI" class="company-name">Standard Lithium</a> and <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/TTI" class="company-name">Tetra Technologies</a> are planning to build capacity in the area. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="728" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/225e9125-35dd-4d6b-a08c-d1ec4738b09d-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> The attraction is what is known as the Smackover formation, a geologic trend that runs from Texas to Florida and is rich with saltwater brine, which once bedeviled companies drilling for oil. That brine also contains small amounts of lithium, and the companies are increasingly optimistic they can scale up technologies to extract it.</p><p> Mining companies&#39; efforts to shore up domestic supplies have run into hurdles in recent years. But companies drilling for lithium say their extraction methods are cleaner than traditional mining, and face fewer regulatory risks.</p><p> In an interview at a lithium demonstration plant near El Dorado, Ark., Standard Lithium Chief Executive</p> Robert Mintak said the Smackover could become as significant to domestic lithium production as the Permian Basin of West Texas and New Mexico has been for US oil output.<p></p><p> “The economics will be better, though,” Mintak said. “And the resource will last longer. There&#39;s a more favorable environment for where the product is going [compared with oil].”</p><p> Tetra Technologies, a company that is planning to extract the chemical bromine from brine in the region, is studying the feasibility of building a plant that would add thousands of tons of lithium extraction capacity, and recently drilled its second test well near Magnolia. “It&#39;s going to be a pretty big boom in Southwest Arkansas,” said Brady Murphy, Tetra&#39;s CEO.</p><p> These are expensive bets. Mintak estimated it currently costs about $1.5 billion to build 25,000 metric tons of capacity, after inflation boosted the prices of construction materials. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="530" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819560?width=700&amp;height=530" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Mayor Parnell Vann is seeking to grow the lithium industry in the small south Arkansas town.</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Vancouver-based Standard Lithium, backed by Koch Industries, is studying the feasibility of building the first commercial US lithium extraction facility, with a capacity of 6,000 metric tons a year. It wants to begin construction in early 2024.</p><p> It has also proposed building a 30,000-ton plant just west of Magnolia, where Mintak said the concentration of lithium is about twice as high as its current location. Construction could potentially begin in the next few years.</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> Put together, the three companies&#39; projects would require around 6,000 jobs and north of 1,600 trucks by 2028, according to a person familiar with the matter.</p><p> An influx of workers and trucks could give Magnolia and nearby counties an economic shot in the arm after years of decline. But the prospect is also concerning, Mayor Vann said, because the town of 12,000 is facing a shortage of new houses, and many of the region&#39;s limited roads, water and sewage systems are unprepared. The town is home to a state college, Southern Arkansas University, but its surrounding areas are largely rural.</p><p> “No one is listening right now,” he said. “But when it blows up, it&#39;s going to be too late.”</p><p> In Magnolia, named for a tree that blooms once or twice a year, a bright two-story mural depicts oil field workers clutching rig equipment and twisting valves, recalling the period when the region was a thriving community hub of oil field activity. That all changed after the 1980s oil bust, and a series of mill closures and company departures in the years since. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819562?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Chad Martin, Standard Lithium&#39;s vice president of US operations, wearing light trousers, talks to engineering manager Will Smith at the company&#39;s plant in Arkansas.</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> “We&#39;ve just about dried up to nothing,” said Valarie Clark, a judge in nearby Lafayette County.</p><p> Now the economic winds are shifting again.</p><p> At Stephens Country Store in Magnolia, manager Edie Mobbs said at least three companies in the past couple of years have asked whether they can buy the mineral rights on 80 acres she and her husband own. She has so far decided not to sell, just in case they want to lease the land.</p><p> “I&#39;m wondering if it&#39;s not because somebody knows something we don&#39;t know,” she said.</p><p> Some worry the city&#39;s potential growth could bring crime and drug abuse. Magnolia&#39;s City Council, led by Vann, recently passed an ordinance to install an entertainment district near the town&#39;s main square, which would allow restaurant patrons to carry open containers of alcohol from one venue to another. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="476" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819565?width=700&amp;height=476" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> An oil field pit near a Tetra Technologies brine drill rig outside Magnolia.</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Michael Seabaugh, senior pastor at Magnolia&#39;s Central Baptist Church, said those activities should be kept away from the town&#39;s large churches, just off the square. A few hundred voters agreed, signing a petition aimed at putting the issue up for a ballot vote.</p><p> Seabaugh said area residents have a tendency to feel left behind or passed over.</p><p> “That breeds a cynicism and a desperation,” he said. “Which is what I think is typified in the entertainment district. This is a desperation move.”</p><p> Mark Williams, an owner of Murphy&#39;s Jewelers in Magnolia, is in favor of the entertainment district because he believes it would bring more foot traffic to the town square. And the city needs a way to attract incoming workers, he said.</p><p> Williams said he can recall one company decades ago that gave up on pumping oil from his family&#39;s land because of the large amounts of saltwater bubbling from the earth. That same saltwater is now an asset. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="481" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819564?width=700&amp;height=481" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Members of Magnolia&#39;s Central Baptist Church congregation have opposed plans to add a local entertainment district.</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> “It&#39;s amazing how things can turn in 40 years,” he said.</p><p> Exxon believes it can leverage its engineering prowess to become a low-cost domestic supplier of lithium, and has had discussions with battery and EV manufacturers, people familiar with the matter said. The company would also benefit from green-energy subsidies <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/climate-legislation-inflation-reduction-act-small-towns-eb0ce798?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">included in the Inflation Reduction Act</a> , which allows for tax credits of 10% of the cost of producing lithium.</p><p> Exxon, which is generally <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chevron-cvx-exxon-xom-q1-earnings-report-2023-6a022a3d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">bullish about the future of oil and natural gas</a> , is also preparing for a future less dependent on gasoline. Last year, it projected light-duty vehicle demand for internal combustion engine fuels could peak by 2025, while EVs, hybrids and vehicles powered by fuel cells could grow to more than 50% of new car sales by 2050.</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>What is your outlook on the potential for US oil and gas companies to extract lithium? Join the conversation below.</em></p></div></div><p> Not that anyone in Magnolia would ever be caught dead in one. For all the town buzz about lithium, local officials, shopkeepers and others said they couldn&#39;t see themselves driving an EV.</p><p> “They don&#39;t appeal to me whatsoever,” said Columbia County Judge Doug Fields. But Fields noted Magnolia is poised to get its first EV charging stations soon, just outside of town square.</p><p> “I don&#39;t mind them parking there,” he said with a laugh. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=78BE4563-8D74-4B28-9FC7-450D5330107C&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fthis-arkansas-town-could-become-the-epicenter-of-a-u-s-lithium-boom-54ad7306&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Demand for lithium is expected to outpace global supply as consumers switch to battery-powered vehicles. With China currently leading in processing of the vital raw material, the US government is looking to boost domestic production. Photo illustration: Carlos Waters/WSJ<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>Write to Collin Eaton at <a href="mailto:collin.eaton@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">collin.eaton@wsj.com</a> and Benoît Morenne at <a href="mailto:benoit.morenne@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">benoit.morenne@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/this-arkansas-town-could-become-the-epicenter-of-aus-lithium-boom-54ad7306</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/this-arkansas-town-could-become-the-epicenter-of-aus-lithium-boom-54ad7306<author><![CDATA[Collin EatonBenoît Morenne]]></author><category> WSJ公司</category><category>gfx-contrib</category><category>专有的</category><category>Energy</category><category>机动车</category><category>替代燃料汽车</category><category>汽车</category><category>Fossil Fuels</category><category> Integrated Oil/Gas</category><category> Oil and Gas</category><category>输出/生产</category><category>容量/设施</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>产品与服务</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Exxon Mobil</category><category> XOM</category><category> Standard Lithium</category><category> SLI.V</category><category> CA:SLI</category><category> Tetra Technologies</category><category> TTI</category><category> Parnell Vann</category><category>输出</category><category>生产</category><category>容量</category><category>设施</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>产品</category><category>服务</category><category>energy</category><category>机动车</category><category>替代燃料汽车</category><category>汽车</category><category>fossil fuels</category><category> integrated oil</category><category> gas</category><category> oil and gas </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘They Smooth Out Every Curve.’ Why Popcorn Swimsuits Are Everywhere This Summer.]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Textured &#39;crinkle&#39; bikinis and one-pieces are supremely soft, stretchy and flattering. Here, a guide. <figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-817665/?width=2000&amp;size=1.5" alt="POP IT LIKE IT’S HOT Our model willingly sprawled out on a ‘beach’ of real popcorn to showcase this trio of comfy, flattering crinkle suits." referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption> POP IT LIKE IT&#39;S HOT Our model willingly sprawled out on a &#39;beach&#39; of real popcorn to showcase this trio of comfy, flattering crinkle suits. <span></span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001036320"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001036320"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name">Grace Cook</span> / Photography by F. Martin Ramin/The Wall Street Journal, <span class="author" itemprop="name">Styling by Lizzy Wholley</span> , <span class="author" itemprop="name">Prop Styling by Mieko Takahashi</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 20, 2023 7:00 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/they-smooth-out-every-curve-why-popcorn-swimsuits-are-everywhere-this-summer-bc5ecc5b"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p> <strong>UNLESS YOU&#39;RE</strong> describing a Shar-Pei, “crumpled” and “wrinkly” aren&#39;t typically flattering modifiers. But swimsuits in crinkle fabric have emerged as one of summer&#39;s top styles. Sydney Kempler, 30, a Houston marketing specialist and a “big fan,” owns eight versions by brands such as PacSun and <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/SE/XSTO/HM.B" class="">H&amp;M</a> <span class="company-name-type">.</span> Plush and stretchy, their material, said Kempler, “smooths every lump and bump.”</p><p> In the 1980s and &#39;90s, a label called Hunza first popularized crinkle suits&#39; tactile textile, often referred to as “popcorn” or “seersucker” fabric. It got a little help from Julia Roberts, who wore Hunza&#39;s crimped blue-and-white cutout dress in “Pretty Woman.” Relaunched in 2015 as Hunza G by current London creative director Georgiana Huddart, the brand&#39;s suits have become go-tos for It girls like Kendall Jenner and Dua Lipa. Now, labels from Bottega Veneta to Good American have jumped on the rumpled beachwear train. And women are paying attention. Online-shopping platform Lyst reported a 6% rise in searches for “textured swimwear” between January and July of this year.</p><p> Kempler said she finds popcorn fabrics look dressier and “more expensive” than flat, flimsy Lycra, which can pill and sag easily. She recently paired a crinkled ecru maillot with linen pants to head straight to a bar after some beach time. But Sabra Krock, creative director of swimwear retailer Everything But Water, said the real draw of crinkle suits is their excellent elasticity: “They&#39;re so accommodating for many different shapes and sizes.” </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="wsj-article-pullquote article__inset__pullquote "><p class="pullquote-content article__inset__pullquote__quote"> <span class="l-qt article__inset__pullquote__mark--left">“</span> Popcorn fabrics can look dressier and &#39;more expensive&#39; than flat, flimsy Lycra. <span class="r-qt article__inset__pullquote__mark--right">”</span></p></div></div><p> Knitted from proprietary nylon-elastane yarn, Hunza G&#39;s suits “stretch to fit” without “stretching out,” claims Huddart. Her malleable bikinis and maillots are generally one-size-fits-most, an approach rival brands have adopted. Devyani Ramani, a New York COO of a fashion wholesaler who is in her 30s, bought a wrinkled Hunza G one-piece in her third trimester of pregnancy. She&#39;s confident it will expand to fit now and, once baby&#39;s arrived, snap back to serve her for summers to come.</p><p> Kristen Cleary, owner of the Los Angeles store Coast by Coast, said that one-size suits take the anxiety-inducing guesswork out of swimwear searches. For her part, Huddart views standard swim sizing as flawed, noting that many shoppers end up sizing up. But, at 6&#39;3”, she did concede that tall women can sometimes struggle with the length of Hunza&#39;s one-size pieces. To solve this crinkle crisis, she launched Hunza G&#39;s Coverage Collection in June, elongated versions of its signature silhouettes made with extra fabric.</p><p> Although Krock is a wrinkle-waterwear advocate, she&#39;s skeptical that the suits can accommodate all body types. “Women with bigger busts might struggle with the general lack of underwire support,” she said. “And petite women, noted Huddart, could feel overwhelmed with the density of the fabric in a one-piece.” For the latter group, Huddart suggests popcorn bikinis with strapless tops or fine straps. Women who are tall, curvy or both might prefer separates, too, she added.</p><p> Even so, Cleary said that her customers at Coast to Coast “rarely” return popcorn purchases, and that one-size suits can be especially helpful for online shoppers. When it comes to standard suits, Ramani said she ordinarily orders a style in two or three sizes and returns what doesn&#39;t fit. Her single popcorn piece, however, provided instant gratification. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><h3> SAGE CHOICE</h3><p> A just-skin-baring-enough monokini in an enviable green hue. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="700" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-816989?width=700&amp;height=700" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"></figcaption></figure></div><p> Swimsuit, <em>$99,</em> <a href="https://www.goodamerican.com/products/always-fits-monokini-chartrusse001" target="_blank" class="icon none"><em>GoodAmerican</em></a> ; Earrings, <em>$195</em> , Necklace, <em>$345,</em> <a href="https://www.lizziefortunato.com/" target="_blank" class="icon none"><em>Shop.LizzieFortunato.com</em></a> ; Jia Jia Necklace, <em>$700,</em> <a href="https://www.matchesfashion.com/us/products/Jia-Jia-Turquoise%2C-tiger%27s-eye-%26-14kt-gold-necklace-1449540" target="_blank" class="icon none"><em>MatchesFashion.com</em></a> ; Necklace, <em>$380,</em> <a href="https://jiajiajewelry.com/collections/sale/products/arizona-tigers-eye-long-necklace" target="_blank" class="icon none"><em>JiaJiaJewelry.com</em></a> ; Necklace, <em>$1,250,</em> <a href="https://www.davidyurman.com/womens/necklaces/box-chain-necklace-in-18k-yellow-gold-1.7mm-CH0306+88.html" target="_blank" class="icon none"><em>DavidYurman.com</em></a> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><h3> STRING FLING</h3><p> The super-skinny straps on this one-size-fits-most option won&#39;t leave you with irksome tanlines (also, don&#39;t forget sunscreen). </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
